<br>
Also, an Ogre was killing Kelethin guards on a bridge earlier today, and managed to slay one before he was offed by another. I looted the dead guard of it's Round Shield and sold it; the corpse would've decayed five and a half minutes later, clearly not enough time for said Ogre to return, and he was probably at such a level that he didn't care about the equipment or the 1.4 platinum generated from selling it.<br>
<br>
Am I a player to be despised? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 387<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 1:09:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2247.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is one man's trash another man's treasure?</span><hr size=1> If the corpse has become &quot;open&quot; for anyone to loot, then loot it. The other person has had plenty of opportunity to take the loot if they want it. If scavenging were wrong, then the corpse would just poof instead of becoming open. Unless they're standing right there clearly engaged in some kind of extended battle and just haven't had a chance to loot yet. Exercise common sense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 1:16:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2247.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> If someone is fighting next to the rotting ..</span><hr size=1> .. corpses, it's usually nice to ask first -- depending on the fight, things might go public before the group can loot.  Hoovering up under a groups feet as they fight is pretty greedy.  Few will much care about &quot;vendor&quot; loot left to rot, but for nice stuff on high level MOBs, it could even get you suspended or banned (seen that on SH in MM).  If no one is anywhere near, it's all obviously fair game. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
